JOHANNESBURG - Retail chain Clicks, is expanding its market share, adding almost 90 more shops with the help of an extended footprint in Netcare hospitals.Clicks now has 600 stores, with the hospital group housing 41 of the new stores. The health retailer also grew its pharmacy network to over 450 outlets in the past 6 months.The company has set aside just over R500-million for capital investments this year.Clicks half-year income increased by 11 percent, to R13.5-billion. eNCA